the supreme court today refused to throw out 
an indictment accusing new york city hotel owners harry and leona 
helmsley of federal income tax evasion 
the court without comment let stand a ruling that dismissed 
the helmsleys challenge to the 47count indictment 
todays action comes less than a week after the high court in 
an unrelated case limited the right of criminal defendants to 
challenge indictments before trial 
the justices on march 28 ruled that federal criminal defendants 
who fail to persuade a judge to throw out their indictments because 
of alleged misconduct by prosecutors cannot appeal before they are 
tried and convicted 
the helmsleys appeal raised the same issue 
they were indicted with two hotel executives a year ago on 
charges they evaded some 12 million in federal taxes over a 
threeyear period 
