for a presidential merit schools program of cash awards to 
public and private elementary schools that have made substantial 
progress in raising student educational achievement creating a 
safe and drugfree environment and reducing the dropout rate 
another 100 million would create a new magnet schools of 
excellence program to set up or enhance magnet schools to 
strengthen academic and vocational offerings as well as promote 
open enrollment and parental choice bushs program would be 
separate from an existing magnet schools program designed to 
achieve desegregation 
bush is also proposing 25 million apiece for programs of 
emergency grants to urban schools with the nations most severe 
drug problems and grants to states to develop alternative ways to 
certify teachers and principals 
