<TEXT>
here is a brief overview of the 23year 
war in namibia between the south africanled security forces and 
the guerrillas of the southwest africa peoples organization 
origin swapo began military operations in 1966 after south 
africa defied a united nations resolution to relinquish control of 
the territory it had captured from the germans in world war i an 
estimated 20000 people mostly swapo guerrillas have been killed 
fighting almost all the fighting has taken place in northern 
namibia and involved bush battles and sabotage attacks carried out 
by swapo forces that infiltrated from bases in southern angola 
swapo has never been able to establish permanent bases inside 
namibia and only a small number of guerrillas have been active in 
the territory at any time until the fighting in recent days both 
sides had observed an informal ceasefire since august 
size south african military officials estimate swapo has 8000 
members in its military wing swapo says it also has 80000 
supporters at refugee camps outside namibia although the un has 
put the figure at about 60000 
south africa had an estimated 50000 troops in namibia 
concentrated in the north the figure includes namibians belonging 
to the southwest africa territorial force the number must be 
reduced to 12000 by midmay and 1500 by july 1 under the peace 
accords signed last december 
also south africa has agreed to cut the territorial police 
force from 8300 to 6000 during the independence process 
the united nations has authorized 4650 peacekeeping troops for 
the operation but only about 1000 have arrived 
angola in the civil war in neighboring angola 50000 cuban 
troops have supported the marxist government in its fight against 
