called for parkin to receive 150000 over two years for his 
services the prosecutor said 
kaub was teledyne electronics executive vice president dealing 
with government contracts sullivan and his successor schnittjer 
were also executive vice presidents 
lawyers for the three men denied that their clients had done 
anything wrong and argued that they were victims of a conspiracy 
between parkin and his associates 
