the frontier by midmorning the austrian automobile and touring 
club reported 
on saturday hungarys customs duties will rise from from 30 
percent to 45 a special low rate of 15 percent for computers and 
video machines will end and dutyfree allowances will be reduced 
sharply 
under current rules each member of a family of four may bring 
back dutyfree goods worth 200 on each trip and the shares may be 
combined to cover a major purchase on saturday the perperson 
allowance will be cut in half and no totaling will be allowed 
official figures in budapest say hungarians spent the equivalent 
of about 600000 in austria between january 1988 when visafree 
travel to the west began and feburary of this year 
