on saturday ei du pont de nemours amp co ended 38 years as 
operator of the nations largest nuclear weapons facility turning 
the plant over to westinghouse savannah river co a subsidiary of 
the pittsburghbased parent 
weve been convinced that we can make this a model of 
excellence westinghouse savannah river co president james s 
moore said at a news conference monday 
the savannah river plant which westinghouse renamed the 
savannah river site is the nations only source of tritium a 
highly radioactive gas used at other government defense plants to 
make nuclear warheads 
the three active nuclear reactors at the plant have been shut 
down for nearly a year because of safety and structural problems 
and a series of mishaps in recent months has raised doubts about 
whether improvements are likely anytime soon 
moore said a new name and freshly painted signs at the 
300squaremile complex near aiken will not erase the facilitys 
troubled history 
our first task now that transition is over is to enhance the 
public trust and obviously ensure a safe restart of the 
reactors said moore whose company has a fiveyear contract 
the ultimate way to gain trust is to perform actions speak 
louder than words 
he stressed that westinghouse would not jeopardize safety for 
production 
we are not putting production ahead of safety even if they 
tell us to he said referring to the federal government 
the pentagon has said that unless at least one of the reactors 
is restarted by the end of the year it might have to deactivate 
some warheads to preserve supplies of tritium 
moore said a clause in the companys contract with the 
department of energy allows me to go directly to doe 
headquarters if i feel im being told to do something contrary to 
what we believe is right or safe 
my view is that if i have to do that ive failed on my job 
because ive failed to communicate with my customer here at the 
site 
moore also said he would shut down the reactors if the energy 
department asked for more tritium than could be produced safely in 
the alotted time 
the doe has tied the amount of money westinghouse will be paid 
to how well it performs 
