secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar who briefed security 
council members said three senior diplomats from western nations 
speaking on condition of anonymity 
their findings were incorporated into a report the un chief 
presented to the security council on monday evening under unusually 
heavy security 
more than 1000 swapo guerrillas infiltrated northern namibia 
