since the early days of the vietnam war most daily headlines 
and leading items on the tv evening news have involved moral as 
well as legal choices the pentagon papers the watergate breakin 
the village of my lai pulling the plug on karen ann quinlan lust 
and greed among tv evangelists oliver north hero or villain 
lt col north argues he lied to congress to serve a higher 
good socrates defied the law in refusing to finger fellow 
athenians opposed to the rule of the 30 tyrants from jail cells 
henry thoreau and martin luther king urged disobedience to unjust 
laws jeb magruder said his role model for breaking the law in the 
