smaller firms are calling in experts to help draft a formal code of 
ethics 
chemical banks code of ethics which must be read and 
signed by all its 30000 employees worldwide is among the most 
widely copied to translate the code into an operating 
philosophy more than 250 vice presidents have undergone a 
twoday seminar on decision making and corporate values 
presided over by the banks chairman 
the code is credited with chemicals decision to create a 
special lending unit for minority businesses and its refusal to 
finance arms exporters and corporate raiders or do business with 
pornographers massage parlors and several countries run by 
dictators 
chief executive officer james burke calls johnson and johnsons 
credo which dates back to 1945 the glue that held the 
health care multinational together during two nightmare tylenol 
poisoning incidents and played the most important role in 
withdrawing the capsules 
the credo also dictated managements decision to stop 
advertising their baby oil as a tanning lotion after medical 
evidence showed the product speeded up the suns harming effects on 
the skin sales immediately plunged from 10 million to 5 million 
but again the firm bounced back 
why are ethics suddenly hot now 
in the wake of the scandals in wall street chicagos commodity 
market and defense contracts there is an awareness that the 
company which acts responsibly can avoid fines and jail sentences 
reduce court suits that entail costly legal and accounting fees 
diminish the threat of more government regulation increase company 
morale and attract a higher type more loyal employee 
there is a growing conviction that strong corporate culture 
and ethics are a vital strategic key to survival and profitability 
in a highly competitive era concludes the business roundtable a 
public issues forum for some 200 top chief executive officers 
after an indepth study of the corporate ethics of 10 leading 
firms including boeing chemical bank general mills and xerox 
a few weeks ago new yorks harvard club witnessed an unlikely 
gathering of theologians philosophers and wall street brokers and 
analysts to launch ethics in the financial marketplace by john 
casey managing director of the investment firm scudder stevens 
and clark 
when casey a disciple of chuck powers sat down at his apple ii 
word processor to write a howto guide to responsible business 
behavior friends on wall street joked that it would be one of 
the shortest books ever written 
the rev langan who never disguises the fact he is a jesuit 
priest when going into a firm notes that the yuppie philosophy of 
grab it all quick any which way is somewhat in decline 
some of the fasttrackers are more cautious now that the 
market is less giddy he says also when you see people barred 
for life from the security industry it gives pause to think 
