19thcentury mende society of the guinea coast had a judicial 
system amazingly similar to the american one they had a supreme 
court a district court a circuit court they had appeal witness 
crossexamination and bail 
that allowed me to present cinque not as a kind of dumb savage 
in a situation he doesnt understand but as a man a very 
perplexed man stuck in a situation that he does understand 
