poring over court transcripts recorded in longhand at the archives 
of the us supreme court the library of congress and elsewhere 
but why use the novel form after such painstaking historical 
research 
to dramatize a historical personage who has not entered into 
the mainstream you have to find his personality imagine one for 
him she said then recited a favorite quotation by voltaire 
there is no history only fictions of varying degrees of 
plausibility 
