<TEXT>
fruits and vegetables high in boron like 
apples and broccoli appear to keep bones stronger by preventing 
loss of calcium 
you could drink milk to kingdom come and never get any 
boron said forrest h nielsen director of the department of 
agricultures human nutrition research center in grand forks nd 
nielsen led a study of five men and 10 women who were given a 
lowboron diet for nine weeks then boron supplements for seven 
weeks when the boron was reduced the subjects excreted more 
calcium their bodies werent using it 
when boron was increase there was less calcium in their 
urine and more calcium and an active form of vitamin d in their 
blood he said 
nielsen said nobody knows yet exactly what boron does in the 
body the first studies suggesting that it might be important were 
done in 1987 before 1987 there was no evidence that it might be 
important in human nutrition wed known it was essential to plants 
since 1910 but we still dont know what its biochemical role is 
in plants 
nielsen said he isnt suggesting boron supplements large 
amounts can cause changes similar to osteoporosis brittleness of 
bones resulting from a loss of calcium and a wellbalanced diet 
will include enough he said 
boron is found in broccoli cabbage and other leafy vegetables 
nuts legumes and fruits especially apples pears and grapes he 
said but when you talk about a meat and potatoes and milk and 
