the us dollar fell against the japanese yen 
tuesday morning while share prices rose sharply on the tokyo stock 
exchange 
the nikkei stock average of 225 selected issues which gained 
20339 points monday added another 27606 points or 084 percent 
to finish the morning session at 3331813 another new high 
the dollar which opened at 13163 yen down 063 yen from 
mondays closing was changing hands at about 13140 yen at late 
morning the currency traded in the range of 13120 to 13188 yen 
during the morning 
a communique released monday by the group of seven leading 
industrialized nations in washington in which finance officials 
reaffirmed the desirability of stable currency rates forced the 
us currency lower dealers said 
the dollar also fell in tokyo because of dollarselling by 
european central banks in new york and london overnight traders 
said 
the bank of japan reportedly sold dollars monday for the first 
time since 1985 
but market sentiment in tokyo still favored a strong dollar 
mainly because of higher interest rates in the united states said 
a trader with a major commercial bank in tokyo speaking on 
condition of anonymity 
on the stock market the gain in the dow jones industrial 
average in new york on monday lower oil prices and a strengthening 
of the yen boosted stock buying orders from japanese investors 
said yoshio shimoyama of nikko securities 
he said the yens recent upward move relieved investors 
in addition to individual investors institutional investors 
who had been sitting on the sidelines finally began participating 
and helped make trading active he said 
